# App Routing Structure

This project uses Next.js App Router with route groups for organization:

## Admin Routes
- [/admin/forms](mdc:app/(admin)/admin/forms/page.tsx) - Form management dashboard
- [/admin/forms/add](mdc:app/(admin)/admin/forms/add/page.tsx) - Create new forms
- [/admin/forms/edit/[id]](mdc:app/(admin)/admin/forms/edit/[id]/page.tsx) - Edit existing forms
- [/admin/permissions](mdc:app/(admin)/admin/permissions/page.tsx) - Manage permissions
- [/admin/roles](mdc:app/(admin)/admin/roles/page.tsx) - Manage user roles

## Public Routes
- [/forms/[id]](mdc:app/(public)/forms/[id]/page.tsx) - Public form submission page

The routing is organized into two main route groups:
1. `(admin)` - Protected routes that require authentication and admin permissions
2. `(public)` - Public-facing routes accessible to all users

